    "title": "Quadratic Equations",
    "body": "A quadratic has an x² term. Many factor into (x−r₁)(x−r₂)=0, whose solutions (roots) are r₁ and r₂. The sum of the roots equals −b/a and the product equals c/a, a useful shortcut on the test.",
    "key_points": [
      "Set each factor equal to zero to find the roots.",
      "Sum of roots = −b/a; product of roots = c/a.",
      "Check signs carefully when factoring."
    ],
    "worked_example": "x²−5x+6=0 → (x−2)(x−3)=0 → x=2 or x=3."
